---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Editorial Team | SexualHarassmentCalc';
const description = 'Editorial standards for SexualHarassmentCalc.';
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <h1>Editorial Team</h1>
  <p><em>Reviewed by our editorial team. Updated May 2026.</em></p>

  <p>
    Every page on SexualHarassmentCalc is written or reviewed by our editorial team before publication, drawing on general knowledge of employment-discrimination intake, EEOC procedure, and state fair-employment-agency practice. We do not publish unreviewed content.
  </p>

  <h2>Editorial standards</h2>
  <p>
    The site follows five rules. They are not aspirational &mdash; they are the rules a page must satisfy before it is published.
  </p>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Cite real authority.</strong> Statutes by U.S.C. section, cases by name and reporter cite, EEOC guidance by document name. No paraphrased legal &ldquo;rules&rdquo; without a source.</li>
    <li><strong>No legal advice.</strong> Every page is informational. The calculator outputs an educational range, not a case value. We do not represent any reader and no attorney-client relationship is formed by reading or contacting the site.</li>
    <li><strong>Plain language, not jargon.</strong> If a term requires explanation (<em>quid pro quo</em>, <em>Faragher</em>/<em>Ellerth</em>, constructive discharge), we define it the first time it appears on each page.</li>
    <li><strong>Dated reviews.</strong> Each page shows the month/year of its last review. We revisit dated pages when material law changes (Speak Out Act, EEOC strategic plan updates, major Supreme Court decisions).</li>
    <li><strong>Direct the reader out.</strong> Every guide ends with a clear pointer: EEOC field-office locator, state agency, or an instruction to consult a plaintiff-side employment attorney before any deadline passes.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Corrections policy</h2>
  <p>
    If you spot a factual error, an out-of-date statute or case cite, or a worked example that no longer reflects current law,
    email <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a> with the page URL and the correction. We update
    promptly and add a dated note at the bottom of the affected page when the correction is substantive.
  </p>
</BaseLayout>
